OL,3,CWales to stick to 20mph but there will
OL,4,Cbe 'adjustments', says Cabinet
OL,5,CSecretary
OL,7,FMeanwhile, Rhun ap Iorwerth, Leader of
OL,8,FPlaid Cymru, said he supports the
OL,9,Fprinciple of widespread 20mph zones
OL,10,Fbut believes it was "implemented very
OL,11,Fpoorly and inconsistently, with too
OL,12,Fmany roads changing to 20mph in places
OL,13,Fwhere it felt unreasonable."
OL,15,FHe said: "Welsh Government must push
OL,16,Fahead now and sort it out, working
OL,17,Fwith local authorities and communities
OL,18,Fto ensure that limits are properly
OL,19,Freviewed, and unreasonable 20mphs are
OL,20,Fremoved."
